<concept
  id="conceptId">
  <title>Word-to-DITA Style-to-Tag Mapping Video Tutorial</title>
  <shortdesc>A video tutorial on setting up a non-trivial style-to-tag mapping for a typical technical document.</shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>word-to-DITA transform<indexterm>video tutorial</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>tutorials<indexterm>word-to-DITA video tutorial</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <conbody>
    <p>This video tutorials works through the start-to-finish process of creating a new style-to-tag mapping for a Word document that represents a typical technical document that becomes a tree of topics with concepts and tasks.</p>
    <note>This video predates release 0.9.16 and so shows using <xmlatt>styleId</xmlatt> rather than
        <xmlatt>styleName</xmlatt>. You should prefer <xmlatt>styleName</xmlatt> rather than
        <xmlatt>styleId</xmlatt>. It also predates the switch from <xmlelement>style</xmlelement> to
        <xmlelement>paragraphStyle</xmlelement> and <xmlelement>characterStyle</xmlelement>. The
      basic concepts are still relevant but the markup details are out of date.</note>
    <note>
      <p>The video is served from the Screencast.com site.</p>
    </note>
    <p d4p_renditionTarget="pdf epub" deliveryTarget="pdf epub">The video tutorial is at <xref keyref="website-word2dita-video-tutorial"
/> on the Screencast site.</p>
